<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920304-0104</DOCNO><DOCID>920304-0104.</DOCID><HL>   International:   British Aerospace Contract</HL><DATE>03/04/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A7</SO><CO>   U.BA</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><NS>DEFENSE CONTRACTS (DFC)</NS><RE>EUROPE (EU)GREAT BRITAIN (UK)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   LONDON -- The British government awarded a contract valuedat #570 million ($999.1 million) to British Aerospace PLC tosupply advanced short-range air-to-air missiles to the RoyalAir Force.   The missiles will be fitted to the RAF's Harrier jetfighters and the European Fighter Aircraft, which iscurrently under development by a European consortiumincluding Britain and will come into RAF service by the endof the decade, said Tom King, secretary of state for defense.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>